## Architecture

```
packages/shared    ← IPC contracts, Zod schemas, types (no UI, no Node)
packages/ui        ← @ajh/ui: React component library (no app logic)
packages/prompts   ← AI prompt templates (pure TS)
packages/core/ai/data/workers ← main process only — NEVER import in renderer
apps/desktop       ← Electron app (main + preload + renderer)
```

Renderer ↔ main communication: `window.api.*` only (via service hooks, never directly).

---

## Import rules — enforced by ESLint

### Package entrypoints only — no deep local paths

```ts
// ❌ BANNED by ESLint
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/Button';
import { ButtonProps } from '@/components/ui/Button';

// ✅ REQUIRED
import { Button } from '@ajh/ui';
import type { ButtonProps } from '@ajh/ui';
```

`components/ui/` contains only `UpdateBanner` (app-specific) and legacy shims.
Do not create new files there. All shared UI lives in `packages/ui` → `@ajh/ui`.

### Prefer inferred prop types

```ts
// ✅ Best
type Props = React.ComponentProps<typeof Button>;

// ✅ OK when extending
import type { ButtonProps } from '@ajh/ui';
interface MyButtonProps extends ButtonProps { label: string; }

// ❌ Unnecessary
import type { ButtonProps } from '@ajh/ui';
function fn(p: ButtonProps) {}  // use React.ComponentProps instead
```

Import named types only when extending them or when they're non-component types
(`ToastVariant`, `ThemeId`, `ToastItem`).

### Import ordering (auto-fixed by `pnpm lint:fix`)

```ts
// 1. node: built-ins
import { readFile } from 'node:fs';
// 2. external packages
import { motion } from 'framer-motion';
// 3. @ajh/* packages
import { Button } from '@ajh/ui';
// 4. @/ app aliases
import { useJobs } from '@/services';
// 5. relative
import { helper } from './utils';
```

### Always `import type` for type-only imports

```ts
// ❌
import { MyType } from './types';
// ✅
import type { MyType } from './types';
```

